name: PHOENIX AERO CLUB
about: The PHX Aero Club, established in coordination with Phoenix Sky Harbor International Airport, aims to bring together aviation industry enthusiasts for networking and education. Founded on the principles of the first Aero Club in Washington D.C. in 1909, the PHX Aero Club fosters interest in aeronautics and honors eminent airmen. The club offers a forum for interaction among aviation-minded individuals and organizations, encourages education and career development in aviation, and provides a platform for discussing aviation issues. Membership is open to all Arizona airports, airlines, trade associations, manufacturers, law firms, and aviation enthusiasts. The club hosts various events, including luncheons and seminars, to promote its mission. Join the PHX Aero Club to be part of a vibrant community dedicated to advancing aviation.
